message.content:
1. The liraglutide treatment group showed an increase in 31.13 [17.67, 59.09] with a P value of 0.031.
2. Fasting plasma insulin levels increased in the liraglutide treatment group (104 [51, 123] vs 113 [54, 171] mIU/L).
3. The P value for the increase in fasting plasma insulin levels was 0.015.
4. 60 min plasma insulin levels increased in the liraglutide treatment group (326 [165, 441] vs 471 [334, 717] mIU/L).
5. The P value for the increase in 60 min plasma insulin levels was 0.005.
6. 120 min plasma insulin levels increased in the liraglutide treatment group (401 [193, 560] vs 500 [367, 960] mIU/L).
7. The P value for the increase in 120 min plasma insulin levels was 0.047.
8. Insulin area under the curve (AUCins) increased in the liraglutide treatment group (648 [321, 742] vs 738 [451, 1118] mIU/L).
9. The P value for the increase in insulin area under the curve (AUCins) was 0.005.

messages.content:
Statement: 31.13 [17.67, 59.09], P = 0.031), fasting plasma insulin (104 [51, 123] vs 113 [54, 171] mIU/L, P = 0.015), 60 min plasma insulin (326 [165, 441] vs 471 [334, 717] mIU/L, P = 0.005), 120 min plasma insulin (401 [193, 560] vs 500 [367, 960] mIU/L, P = 0.047), and insulin area under the curve (AUCins) (648 [321, 742] vs 738 [451, 1118] mIU/L, P = 0.005) remarkably increased for patients in the liraglutide treatment group.
